JOHANNESBURG - After many months of frustration, the M2 bridge in Johannesburg is set to reopen. It's been closed for the last eight months for repairs. The reopening will be welcome news to motorists who regularly use the route. READ: Joburg's M2 highway construction to be completed in October The bridge will be only available for use from Monday 4 November. Traffic is still moving slowly on Thursday. JMPD spokesperson Xolani Fihla said the officers who were deployed in areas of congestion would be reassigned including to monitor smash-and-grab hotspots.